article.headline: Potter lifts George Washington over Evansville 78-70
article.linkText: Potter lifts George Washington over Evansville 78-70
article.story: NASSAU, Bahamas -- Armel Potter scored 25 points in going over 1,000 career points as George Washington defeated Evansville 78-70 in the Islands of the Bahamas Showcase on Saturday. Maceo Jack added 22 points for the Colonials. Jamison Battle had 11 points for George Washington (2-4). K.J. Riley scored a career-high 28 points for the Purple Aces (3-3). Artur Labinowicz added 19 points and eight rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
